rules.name: Play a sound while duke jumps

script.script:
--
-- This is the default method of every action. It is called once for every game loop cycle.
--
-- instance is an optional injected object which is a reference to the GameObjectInstance for 
-- which this script is executed.
-- scene is an injected object which is a reference to the GameScene for 
-- which this script is executed.
--

function increaseScoreIn(aCustomProperties) 
    local theCurrentScore = nvl(aCustomProperties.get('score') , 0)
    aCustomProperties.set('score', theCurrentScore + 1)
end    

function proceedGame(aGameTime, aElapsedTimeSinceLastLoop) 

    -- Remove the star from the scene, completely kill it
    scene.removeGameObjectInstance(instance)
    
    -- Increase the level score by 1
    increaseScoreIn(scene.customPropertiesProperty())
    
    -- Do the same with the total score
    increaseScoreIn(game.customPropertiesProperty())

	-- The method must return either STOPPED or CONTINUE_RUNNING
	-- STOPPED will kill the script, it is not invoked the next time
	-- CONTINUE_RUNNING will invoke the skript the next game loop cycle.
	return 'STOPPED'
end
